title.91: Star Wars: Return of the Jedi (1983) #4

description.0: Hercules and Recorder try to protect their new Skrull friend Skyppi from an assassin who exclusively hunts Skrulls, while Apollo tries to escape Zeus’ smiting of the Olympian gods.
description.3: Luke's mission is to head out to other worlds to ask they join the new planetary council. However, he finds himself on a world that won't suffer his intrusion.
description.4: Read the epic conclusion to the legendary Phoenix Saga but with a twist ending!
description.5: "For the first time since he has donned the mantle of the Hobgoblin, the man behind the mask knows fear..." Spider-Man engages in his final duel with the Hobgoblin!
description.6: Times are looking bright for our heroes as both old and new members return to the place where all began, the Avengers Mansion. But when the Vision detects a near infinite power approaching the Avengers must rally their troops, for darkness is coming!
description.7: The spirit world has been unbalanced! Black Crow has another vision reminding him that as the spirit of old America, he must kill Captain America, the spirit of new America, to balance the scales. The Black Crow must do what must be done! Captain America must die!
description.12: The spirit of an Egyptian slave has Ben Grimm under his telepathic control!
description.16: Dazzler’s Los Angeles stint hits a snag when a natural disaster strikes!
description.17: Crossbow has a new victim in his sights—and it’s someone connected to Daredevil. Iron Man: Tony Stark makes a cameo appearance!
description.18: Who is behind the menacing force that continues to plague Rhodey?
description.20: The Thing and Mole Man team up to stop the not-so-hot plan of Alden Mass! Meanwhile, Sue is experiencing a painful pregnancy. What could this mean for the Richards' unborn child?
description.21: To save the Colossus, Kitty must marry Caliban! A wedding is one thing, but can Kitty really spend the rest of her life in the catacombs?
description.23: With world destruction as his goal, Doombringer lives up to his name! Will Power Man and Iron Fist be able to stop him?
description.24: The secrets of the first ever SECRET WARS event!
description.25: What a homecoming! When Han, Princess Leia and Artoo return to Tatooine to tie up some unfinished business, it's hardly business as usual-when some of Tatooine's deadliest surviving citizens form the welcoming committee!
description.29: Zeus banished Hercules from Mount Olympus in the name of teaching him humility, but instead it seems his son stumbled upon the things he adores most: action and adventure.
description.30: After a soulful sacrifice, Magik is haunted by the machinations of Belasco's mind. Ghosts from the past emerge, leading Illyana from one dark dimension to another. Will Magik be able to escape Hell itself? And if she remains in the fires of Limbo, will Illyana Rasputin cease to exist?
description.31: Without his Spider-sense, Spider-Man finds another way to track down the Hobgoblin! He attacks his foe, but the Hobgoblin has a surprise up his sleeve and unleashes his ray cannon! Can Spider-Man survive the blasts from such a lethal weapon?
description.32: It's the mighty Avengers versus the magical menace of Morgan Le Fey! With the Mad Witch after the comatose body of Jessica Drew, the Avengers must spring into action to stop her before her plans are complete!
description.33: Attack of the tumbler! In this issue: Captain America and the Tumbler join forces to investigate GLIC offices scandal. Will Captain America be able to help the Tumbler in his goals, and manage to get him to see the errors of his criminal ways?
description.35: Thor, Sif, and Beta Ray Bill have left Asgard far behind as they ride the tides of space searching for Bill's people and the demons who pursue them.
description.37: Four thousand years ago in ancient Egypt, a slave was wrongly tortured to death by the Pharaoh and his wife. Now, in New York City, the spirit of that slave dwells within the form of Ben Grimm.
description.39: Mystical artist Claude von Moore turns his canvas toward a new subject—Doctor Stephen Strange! A commonplace haunting turns into something completely unexpected.
description.41: Daredevil must withstand the tomfoolery of the “Trump”! Murdock defends an old “acquaintance” in court.
description.42: A mysterious new enemy awaits Iron Man's arrival in Cairo.
description.45: Johnny participates in a near-fatal race in California. And while trying to save his friend...Ben must duke it out with Mole Man!
description.46: Kitty needs the Fantastic Four to save Colossus' life! And while out on a date, Kurt and Amanda are ambushed by the Brotherhood!
description.48: In a battle between the Hobgoblin and Spider-Man, an improved version of the Green Goblin's gas defeats the web-slinger! Only one man can save his life...and he is far from a hero!
description.49: Spider-Woman is trapped on the Astral Plane! When the missing Spider-Woman's body is found, Dr. Strange and Hank Pym rush to revive her body. With Spider-Woman's astral self transfixed between dimensions, is there any hope for her survival?
description.50: While Cap and company go about their daily lives without a single crime in sight, Baron Zemo and Mother Superior join forces to bring about a terrible act of villainy our heroes will never see coming. Who will survive the shadows of the night?
description.53: Scarlet Witch guest-stars! Under the guise of "Ms. Wonderly", Scarlet Witch recruits Power Man and Iron Fist to safeguard the Twin Idol of Zor!
description.55: Wolverine fan? Don’t miss this special preview about Wolverine and Kitty Pryde’s limited series from 1984!
description.56: The search for Tay Vanis ends! C3PO finds true love at last-but there's a tragic twist!
description.57: As Belasco's grip tightens over Magik, and she slips further into corruption, Storm's resolve to rescue her apprentice strengthens. Cat continues to devolve into a full feline- what will be left of the woman that was? Illyana must make a fateful choice for her very soul. Will Magik's innocence be her salvation?
description.61: The Thing gets a bird’s-eye view of New York City as he scales the Empire State Building. All to chase down the bank robbing Swede, Goody Two-Shoes!
description.65: Find out who Cloak and Dagger really are and how they came to be! Prepare for the origin of Marvel's mysterious crimefighting duo.
description.67: Fairytales ‘round the campfire with Marvel’s mightiest mutants! Illyana spins a tale about Kitty Pryde and her Space Dragon Lockheed. Wolverine and Nightcrawler also make an appearance - as heroes taking on the White Queen and Black King!
description.68: The first appearance of Micah Synn! But what does this villainous foe want with Daredevil?
description.69: What is the repercussion of Tony Stark's dismissal from the Avengers? A group of local kids in Brooklyn lose their hero.
description.72: The Trial of Reed Richards. By rescuing Galactus from death, the universe penalizes Mr. Fantastic for condemning other planets to death. What will be the final verdict?
description.73: It's Mystique versus the X-Men! And the shapeshifter has the upper hand this time. Everybody dies!
description.74: Black Cat co-stars in artist Fred Hembeck's visionary takeover of Peter Parker's titular series! Spidey and Felicia discuss their relationship... and not just as crimefighters.
description.79: A surprise cameo from Marvel editor Ralph Macchio! Will Alison ditch her old manager Harry Osgood for the promise of fame and fortune?
description.81: The Kid Who Collected Spider-Man. This tale of true heroism touches the heart of all who read it.
description.82: You're not going to want to miss this hilarious issue! It's the Avengers on Late Night with David Letterman!
description.83: As Cap rushes to warn the S.H.E.I.L.D. about Albert DeVoor's Operation: Purge, the world's heroes; the Avengers, the X-Men, and the Fantastic Four must rally together to save the world from its dystopian future!
description.85: With Power Man and Iron Fist out of commission, Colleen Wing and Misty Knight take over to stop the assassin Impasse.
description.86: From a galaxy far, far away… Get the inside scoop on the Star Wars series that redefined Marvel Comics in the 80s.
description.90: Cat, the Kitty Pryde of Limbo, has become the protector of Magik. But will Cat be able to save Illyana from Limbo's many demons and temptations? Nightcrawler of Limbo proves much different than his X-Men counterpart. Belasco has seized Illyana as his own, but will Storm allow it?
description.91: The Rebels attempt to destroy the Death Star II while Luke Skywalker duels with Darth Vader.
description.92: All new adventures of the world famous characters from the greatest science fantasy epic ever! You won't believe the car chase this issue with Lando and a drunken Wookiee, as the search for Han Solo continues!
description.96: The battle between the Puppet Master and the Thing rages on…within Ben Grimm's mind!
description.98: Illyana Rasputin is a young girl who has seen much. The younger sister of the mutant Colossus, Illyana has spent half her life trapped in the realm of Limbo, a hellish purgatory ruled by the demon Belasco. In this strange, satanic world, one hope exists- an alternate dimension Storm, here to save Illyana from serving as Belasco's consort. Will Storm of Limbo be able to reclaim her apprentice's youth? Or has Illyana become too much of Magik, her demonic, unrestrained self?
description.99: Cloak's dark hunger has grown to insurmountable levels. There is only one way to stop his need to consume, and that is for Dagger to offer up her light. All of it.

0.text: Hercules and Recorder try to protect their new Skrull friend Skyppi from an assassin who exclusively hunts Skrulls, while Apollo tries to escape Zeus’ smiting of the Olympian gods.

9.text: After the Hulk is shot at in an airport, he rebuilds his assailant’s hometown which Banner destroyed accidentally as the Hulk.

10.text: New York City, on a crisp, blue morning, watches as a powerful figure, long absent from the busy metropolis, soars overhead... What has brought the Thunder God to the Big Apple!

11.text: Northstar and Aurora fight against Deadly Ernest, but which way will the tides turn when Nemesis joins the fray?

12.text: The spirit of an Egyptian slave has Ben Grimm under his telepathic control!

13.text: First, Natasha employs all the spy decoys she can against Snapdragon in "The Widow...Alone"! Then, Fandral, Volstagg and Hogun contribute to the mythic lore of Asgard in "Ballad of the Warriors Three"!

15.text: The Defenders take on their most surprising foes yet…the NEW MUTANTS!?

19.text: Amara is still struggling to control her powers, and is none too happy about it! Will Kitty Pryde, the X-Woman known as Ariel, be able to console her? Also, Amara finally gets her own codename!

28.text: Doctor Strange guest-stars! There is more to be uncovered about Marc’s psychic link to the Moon God Khonshu, perhaps an entirely new side to the avatar altogether. Marlene faces danger at the hands of a dead magician.

29.text: Zeus banished Hercules from Mount Olympus in the name of teaching him humility, but instead it seems his son stumbled upon the things he adores most: action and adventure.

34.text: Bruce Banner is transformed into the Hulk unwillingly while under Ringmaster’s mind control!

35.text: Thor, Sif, and Beta Ray Bill have left Asgard far behind as they ride the tides of space searching for Bill's people and the demons who pursue them.

36.text: Northstar is concerned with his sister Aurora's dual-identity crisis-but to Aurora, it's not a problem!

37.text: Four thousand years ago in ancient Egypt, a slave was wrongly tortured to death by the Pharaoh and his wife. Now, in New York City, the spirit of that slave dwells within the form of Ben Grimm.

39.text: Strange and Sara Wolfe attend a magical seminar by self-proclaimed sorcerer Akira Nitobe. Strange enters a skeptic leaves the presentation a true believer. Then, tragedy strikes.

40.text: The Defenders…defeated!? With their hideout destroyed, the heroes are at their lowest…but has that ever stopped them before? Watch the Defenders take the fight to Professor Power - as always, in the Mighty Marvel manner!

43.text: Amara Aquilla joins the New Mutants! But will she be able to control her newfound powers, and if not, who will pay the price?

59.text: He's beaten the cops! He's beaten Captain America! And now he's after the President! He's Electro! Only the Falcon is left to fight him - but Falcon's got his hands full!

60.text: When the Avengers come across the hidden labs of Bruce Banner in the Catskill Mountains, they reach out to Mr. Fantastic and She-Hulk to figure out just what Dr. Banner has been up to. Plus: the shared history of She-Hulk and the Hulk revealed!

61.text: The Thing gets a bird’s-eye view of New York City as he scales the Empire State Building. All to chase down the bank robbing Swede, Goody Two-Shoes!

62.text: Bruce Banner stops by the Marvel office for advice on how to handle General Ross!

63.text: Though Beta Ray Bill can lift Mjolnir and though he is worthy, the mythical weapon belongs to only one...Thor. But there are weapon smiths in Asgard capable of developing a weapon for Bill himself, he need only find them...

64.text: Snowbird is faced with one of the Great Beasts she was made to fight, Kolomaq! Also, learn how Michael Twoyoungman became the hero known as Shaman!

65.text: Find out who Cloak and Dagger really are and how they came to be! Prepare for the origin of Marvel's mysterious crimefighting duo.
Find out who Cloak and Dagger really are and how they came to be! Prepare for the origin of Marvel's mysterious crimefighting duo.

67.text: Fairytales ‘round the campfire with Marvel’s mightiest mutants! Illyana spins a tale about Kitty Pryde and her Space Dragon Lockheed. Wolverine and Nightcrawler also make an appearance - as heroes taking on the White Queen and Black King!

71.text: It's the newly-powered Amara Aquilla vs. Selene, the Black Queen!

77.text: The Web Tightens for Black Widow as Iron Maiden swings into deadly action! Digital issue omits "Marvel Fanfare" story.

78.text: The SECRET EMPIRE has sent a horde of killer robots against the Defenders! Can the super team even defend themselves!?

80.text: The street gang known as the Legion has lost faith in The Falcon, and in defiance has kidnapped the President of the United States! How can Falcon save the President without further alienating the people he's tried so much to help? Featuring the villainy of Electro!

89.text: Following last issue’s devastation, Moon Knight is at a crossroads on whether or not to continue his vigilante career. Guest-starring the X-Men and FF!

93.text: M.O.D.O.K. transforms Kate Waynesboro into Ms. M.O.D.O.K., his new bride!

94.text: Moments ago, Beta Ray Bill, a bionic alien bested the mighty Thor in combat and so won the right to possess Thor's enchanted hammer Mjolnir. But even as he announces his victory before the stunned Asgardians, conflict begins anew!

95.text: There's a drug ring going on in the hospital where Puck is tending his wounds, and it's up to him to put an end to it!

96.text: The battle between the Puppet Master and the Thing rages on…within Ben Grimm's mind!
